5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to public records requests; to require
10 redaction from requested public records information that could
11 be used to initiate a financial transaction; to prohibit the
12 use of public records requested from a local board of
13 education, which contain lists of names and addresses of
14 individuals or entities, for the purpose of soliciting those
15 individuals or entities; to authorize the Attorney General to
16 impose civil penalties for violations; and to authorize the
17 State Board of Education to adopt rules.
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
19 Section 1. When any records relating to a public
20 contract for goods or services are requested from a local
21 board of education pursuant to Article 3 of Chapter 12 of
22 Title 36, Code of Alabama 1975, the public officer having
23 custody of the records shall redact account numbers, tax
24 identification numbers, routing numbers, employee
25 identification numbers, sensitive personally identifying
26 information as defined in Section 8-38-2, Code of Alabama
27 1975, and similar information that may be used to initiate a
28 financial transaction.
Page 1

financial transaction.
SB272 Engrossed
29 Section 2. (a) No person shall knowingly sell, give, or
30 receive any list of names and addresses contained in or
31 derived from public records requested from a local board of
32 education for the purpose of selling or offering for sale any
33 property or service to those individuals or entities listed
34 therein.
35 (b) Any person subject to this section who knowingly
36 violates subsection (a) shall be liable for the payment of a
37 civil penalty in an action brought by the Attorney General not
38 to exceed five hundred dollars ($500) for each violation.
39 (c) If a request is made for public records that
40 contain the names or addresses of individuals or entities
41 which the public officer having custody of the records has
42 reasonable cause to believe may be used in violation of
43 subsection (a), prior to responding to the request, the public
44 officer may require the person requesting the records or
45 information therein to provide, in addition to the
46 certification described in Section 36-12-45(b)(3), Code of
47 Alabama 1975, a written certification that the requester does
48 not intend to, and will not:
49 (1) Use any list of names or addresses contained in or
50 derived from the records or information for the purpose of
51 selling or offering for sale any property or service to any
52 individual or entity listed or to any individual who resides
53 at any address listed; or
54 (2) Sell, give, or otherwise make available to any
55 person any list of names or addresses contained in or derived
56 from the records or information for the purpose of allowing
Page 2

from the records or information for the purpose of allowing
SB272 Engrossed
57 that person to sell or offer for sale any property or service
58 to any individual or entity listed or to any individual who
59 resides at any address listed.
60 (d) This section shall not impose any liability on a
61 public officer having custody of a record for granting access
62 to or providing copies of public records or information
63 containing names and addresses, in good faith compliance with
64 subsection (c), to a person who has made a written request for
65 access to such information and has executed a written
66 certification pursuant to subsection (c).
67 (e) The State Board of Education, by rule, may provide
68 guidance and a model certification form for custodians of
69 public records to implement this section.
70 Section 3. This act shall become effective immediately.
Page 3

